{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "To you, Yahweh, I lift up my soul."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My God, I have trusted in you. Don’t let me be shamed.\nDon’t let my enemies triumph over me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yes, no one who waits for you will be shamed. They will be shamed who deal treacherously without cause."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Show me your ways, Yahweh. Teach me your paths."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Guide me in your truth, and teach me, for you are the God of my salvation."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I wait for you all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, remember your tender mercies and your loving kindness, for they are from old times."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Don’t remember the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions. Remember me according to your loving kindness,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "for your goodness’ sake, Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Good and upright is Yahweh, therefore he will instruct sinners in the way."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He will guide the humble in justice. He will teach the humble his way."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "All the paths of Yahweh are loving kindness and truthto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For your name’s sake, Yahweh, pardon my iniquity, for it is great."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "What man is he who fears Yahweh? He shall instruct him in the way that he shall choose."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "His soul will dwell at ease. His offspring will inherit the land."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The friendship of Yahweh is with those who fear him. He will show them his covenant."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eyes are ever on Yahweh, for he will pluck my feet out of the net."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Turn to me, and have mercy on me, for I am desolate and afflicted."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "The troubles of my heart are enlarged. Oh bring me out of my distresses."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Consider my affliction and my travail. Forgive all my sins."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Consider my enemies, for they are many. They hate me with cruel hatred."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Oh keep my soul, and deliver me. Let me not be disappointed, for I take refuge in you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let integrity and uprightness preserve me, for I wait for you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "God, redeem Israelout of all his troubles."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}